Preconditions:
The input array `arr` must not be null.
The input array `arr` must have at least one element.
The input integer `k` must be non-negative.

Postconditions:
The method returns an integer value representing the minimum total space wasted.
The returned value is non-negative.
The returned value is the minimum possible total space wasted if the array is resized at most `k` times.